        <head xml:id="pl-l4d1c2-Hd1e109">Capitulum 2</head>
        <head xml:id="pl-l4d1c2-Hd1e112" type="question-title">Quid sit Sacramentum.</head>
        <p xml:id="pl-l4d1c2-d1e115"> 
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="pl-l4d1c2-Qd1e117" source="http://scta.info/resource/adcd-l10-d1e1388@130-140">
              Sacramentum est sacrae rei signum </quote>
            <bibl>Augustine, De civitate Dei, X, 4, c. 5 (PL 41, 282)</bibl>
          </cit>.
          Dicitur tamen Sacramentum etiam sacrum secretum, sicut dicitur sacramentum deitatis, ut
          Sacramentum sit sacrum signans et sacrum signatum; sed nunc agitur de Sacramento, secundum
          quod est signum. </p>
        <p xml:id="pl-l4d1c2-d1e124">
          Item, <cit>
            <quote xml:id="pl-l4d1c2-Qd1e126">
              Sacramentum est 
              invisibilis gratiae visibilis forma
            </quote>
            <bibl>Augustinus, Quaestionibus in Pentateuch. III, q. 84 (PL 34, 712)</bibl>
          </cit>. 
        </p>
      </div>
